Terminal Access Controller Access-Control System
Xtacacs(cisco proprietry) and Tacacs+(open standard) are both released by cisco and both are derieved from tacacs.
Its TCP and uses port 49. Users will send request to client which are forwarded to Tacacs Deamon or Tacacs Authentication server.
Username, password, authorization and accounting are all encrypted in Tacacs.

Differences between Radius and Tacacs:

1)Tacacs is more secure since it encrypts the entire authentication process. Radius encrypts just user's password of the packet, remainder is unencrypted.
2)Radius uses UDP(1812 and 1813) while Tacacs uses TCP(49).
3)Radius combines authentication and authorization while Tacacs separates authentication and authorization.
